urant table holding an open menu. Wooden chairs, white tablecloths, and other diners are visible around him. He turns his head and looks toward her, appearing attentive and intrigued. Faint text briefly returns over this restaurant scene: “DISPOSABLE COLOR CONTACTS.”\n\nThe clear contact lens appears again on a fingertip against the blue, softly mottled background. The transparent lens catches the light as it rests near the tip of a finger, emphasizing its thin, curved shape.\n\nThe children’s classroom returns in a close, affectionate moment. The curly-haired adult woman is partly behind two children. A young girl with medium-brown skin and curly hair smiles directly forward; a blonde child’s face is partly visible beside her. A small paint-covered hand, bright red with paint, rests on the smiling girl’s cheek and shoulder, adding a playful splash of color. The girl’s eyes appear light greenish, and she smiles calmly despite the messy hand.\n\nThe woman in the café appears once more. She turns her eyes sideways, then faces more forward, her expression serious and intent before softening slightly. The background remains bright and sunlit with blurred greens and whites, and her face is lit with a pinkish glow.\n\nThe commercial ends on the blue-eyed young woman from earlier, her face mostly in shadow with both bright blue eyes visible. Large white serif text centered over her face reads “FreshLook.” Beneath it, smaller capital letters read “COLOR AND CLEAR DISPOSABLE CONTACTS.” At the bottom, smaller white text reads “See your eye care professional.” She glances upward and sideways with a subtle smile, holding the final image on her vivid blue eyes and the product name.",
